definitions.definition: The act of forming or producing fruit ; the act of fructifying, or rendering productive of fruit; fecundation .
The collective organs by which a plant produces its fruit, or seeds, or reproductive spores.

main_definition: ( botany ) The act of forming or producing fruit ; the act of fructifying, or rendering productive of fruit; fecundation .
